  .panel.panel-default.content.project-div
    div
    .panel-body
      h2(class="project-title") HTML Tags
      p Tags define how the content should be displayed on the page
      p They require an open tag and a closing tag.
      p The specifications for the tag are called attributes and are contained within 
        | the opening tag
      p The content to be displayed is placed between the two tags.
      br
      p
        img(src="/images/tags.png")
      br
      p Some tags are self closing:
      p(class="indent") &#8226 meta
      p(class="indent") &#8226 break
      p(class="indent") &#8226 image
      p(class="indent") &#8226 input
      br
      p Here's a 
        a(href= "http://www.w3schools.com/tags/" target="_blank") list
        |  of HTML tags

  div
  .panel.panel-default.content.project-div
